<strong>Summary</strong>

<ul>
  <li>Forked from <a href="https://github.com/garethhunt/modifyheaders/tree/v0.7.1.1">v0.7.1.1  of "Modify Headers"</a> by <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/user/gareth-hunt/">Gareth Hunt</a><ul>
    <li><a href="http://www.garethhunt.com/modifyheaders/">project home</a>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/garethhunt/modifyheaders">github repo</a>
    <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/modify-headers/">AMO</a></ul>
  <li>The <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-modifyheaders-response/tree/response">"response" branch</a> has been modified from the original/official addon to achieve the following objectives:<ul>
    <li>same UI
    <li>modifies <strong>RESPONSE</strong> headers, rather than REQUEST
    <li>the 2 addons can run side-by-side</ul></ul>

<strong>Comments</strong>

<ul>
  <li>The <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-rewrite"><code>moz-rewrite</code></a> project currently contains 3 addon variations:<ul>
    <li>Javascript (evaluated by <code>Cu.evalInSandbox()</code>):<ul>
      <li>branch: <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-rewrite/tree/js/Cu.evalInSandbox/master"><code>js/Cu.evalInSandbox/master</code></a>
      <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/moz-rewrite-js/">AMO</a></ul>
    <li>Javascript (evaluated by <code>eval()</code>):<ul>
      <li>branch: <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-rewrite/tree/js/eval/master"><code>js/eval/master</code></a>
      <li>not hosted on AMO</ul>
    <li>JSON (parsed by <code>JSON.parse()</code>):<ul>
      <li>branch: <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-rewrite/tree/json/master"><code>json/master</code></a>
      <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/moz-rewrite-json/">AMO</a></ul></ul>
  <li>Any one of these variations makes the functionality of "Modify Headers" feel like a child's toy
  <li>All variations require that the data be input/edited externally. The data is saved to text files, and must obey a format convention.
  <li>Nevertheless, some individuals feel that the format of the input data is too complicated
  <li>This class of user:<ul>
    <li>isn't shy to ask for a tool that is simpler and more user-friendly
    <li>is familiar with "Modify Headers" and comfortable using its UI
    <li>wants a version of "Modify Headers" that can modify response HTTP headers</ul>
  <li>I have no intention to add another branch to <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-rewrite"><code>moz-rewrite</code></a> for the purpose of including a UI to display/edit input data. To do so doesn't solve the problem of complexity.
  <li>Authoring the <a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-modifyheaders-response/tree/response">"response" branch</a> of this fork seemed to be the best all-around solution<ul>
    <li><a href="https://github.com/warren-bank/moz-rewrite"><code>moz-rewrite</code></a> remains intact
    <li><a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/modify-response-headers/">"Modify Response Headers"</a> satisfies the needs for this class of user</ul></ul>
